(1374, 11, 'about-content', '<h4 class=\"text-1 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-color\">Love Wins Every-time Inc. (LWE)</span> was founded with the goal of producing constructive and entertaining products for children. The purpose of LWE’s products is to add memorable fun times to these products, while gently addressing the inevitable adverse issues in life. LWE’s aim is to reach children all around the world with much needed awareness to help them to live mentally and emotionally successful lives… spreading LOVE and not hate</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-2 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-color\">Stella Gain (Stella The Story Teller)</span> is the founder of LWE Inc. She is a professional songwriter, author and entertainer. She is also the writer and designer of The Rainbow Race books and app, a timeless adventure for young children with benefits that can last them a lifetime. Stella’s ambition is to continue to entertain children of all ages. Writing a Netflix series and a blockbuster movie including producing their soundtracks are on her bucket list!</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-3 text-h4\">When times were tough, Stella, a single mother, used her skills to keep her young son involved in constructive activities. Having a child and researching children’s needs led her to discover that the most important time of mental and emotional development for a human being is from the ages of 0-7 years old. Accordingly, whatever a child experiences in these early years, shapes that child into who they will be as an adult. Eventually, she put her studies and ideas together and designed The Rainbow Race. She realized that entertaining kids (with a purpose) helps with their healthy mental and emotional development. After observing and being around many children, she focused on some of the trying times that almost all children will face during childhood. To help build her vision, Stella contacted associates who believed in her work. Hence, The Rainbow Race was produced by a group of generous and talented people, who unconditionally used their skills to help entertain and benefit little children.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-4 text-h4\">Children are the future of the world! We are looking forward to contributing to a healthy future world!</h4>\r\n<h5 class=\"text-5 text-head\">THE EARLY TIMES</h5>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-6 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Travis:</span> is a proficient music and vocal producer. However, when approached with this project, he discovered he was also a gifted cartoonist! He used his unique talents to help the vision of The Rainbow Race stories materialize. This included the production of illustrations and songs. Travis continues to produce music tracks for professional artists and other up-and-coming artists of the future. <span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"###\">(See song reviews/comments)</a></span></h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-7 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">THE RAINBOW RACE KIDS</span> represent all the different races of children around the world. The Rainbow Race kids represent “the human race” or let’s say “one race” of kids who LOVE everyone and do not discriminate. They choose to stay respectful and positive no matter what, and they will not change these values especially due to the color of someone’s skin or where they come from.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-8 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Benjamin:</span> was 7 years old, when he worked on The Rainbow Race. He sang and portrayed its songs and stories. He is African American and Brazilian. Benjamin has grown to 6ft 10 inches tall!! He is an honor student and loves to play basketball with the goal of going pro! He was also a senior in the Class of 2020, which was greatly affected by the coronavirus. He was unfortunately not able to finish his senior year physically in school. Follow Benjamin’s journey on Instagram: <span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"###\">@Benjamin.Todd</a></span>. Benjamin is the first Rainbow Race kid to graduate high school. We will follow up with the other Rainbow Race kids, when they also graduate.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-9 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Nehemiah</span> was 6 years old when he worked on The Rainbow Race. He sang and portrayed its songs and stories. He is African American. Nehemiah is an honor student and is currently still in high school. He loves to play basketball.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-10 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Taliana </span>was 5 years old when she worked on The Rainbow Race. She sang and portrayed its songs and stories. She is Italian. Taliana moved back to Italy just before the pandemic and is still in school in Italy.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-11 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Alexis House</span> was 14 years old when she worked on The Rainbow Race. Alexis is American. She made a guest appearance singing on the 7th book, “If you Want to be a Winner!” Alexis is going to school to become an MRI Tech.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-12 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Roman</span>was a coordinator and advisor for The Rainbow Race. He recognized the vision of The Rainbow Race and helped to produce a version in actual storybooks and DVDs. He used his skills and contacts to make this happen. Ultimately, he agreed that an app was the sign of the times and the way to go. Therefore, The Rainbow Race changed its course with the help of his associate, Luis. Roman is currently a financial advisor.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-13 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Luis:</span> is a talented artist, designer and computer programmer. He also recognized the vision of The Rainbow Race and utilized his spare time and talents to reconstruct its storybooks and songs in order for them to be sold on DVD. He also developed the features in order for it to be adapted into an app. Luis is currently in the United States Air Force. His goals are to finish his Bachelors Degree in occupational education while continuing to progress in his Air Force career.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-14 text-h4\">Through the ups and downs of life, The Rainbow Race was put on hold for a few years, though its timeless stories and songs were able to stand the test of time.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-15 text-h4\">A few years later…</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-16 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Yossi</span> An energetic young businessman and website designer, who worked for a company that produced apps, was excited by the vision of The Rainbow Race. He introduced it to his company and production began. Moreover, during The Rainbow Race’s hiatus, LWE Inc. enhanced its features by designing exciting games to go along with the stories, which made the project even more attractive and stimulating. Sadly, midway through the project, Yossi’s company folded.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-17 text-h4\">Once again, through the ups and downs of life, The Rainbow Race was put on hold… but never forgotten!</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-18 text-h4\">Recent Times, December 2019:</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-19 text-h4\"><span class=\"text-style\">Jared </span> is an associate of Yossi’s. Yossi did not forget his promise of completing The Rainbow Race website and app for LWE Inc. Consequently, Jared updated the storybooks and illustrations of all 7 books. In order for it to finally launch, he also helped to finish building the app and website including the exciting features that come with The Rainbow Race. Jared now manages and takes care of all aspects of the app for LWE Inc.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\" text-20 text-h4\">Midway through the final phase of The Rainbow Race’s reinvention in 2020, the now extraordinary historical events mentioned earlier gave LWE the added motivation that it needed to finish The Rainbow Race app ASAP… never allowing an obstacle to block its course it again. Though numerous obstacles kept on coming, LWE’s RACE to the finish line persevered and was finalized on September 7th 2020, which also happens to be Stella Gain’s mother’s birthday…A very important day to her in every way. Now all children everywhere, along with their parents and guardians, if they CHOOSE, can enjoy The Rainbow Race for hours on end!</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-21 text-h4\">The Rainbow Race is a perfect example of one of its own concepts of “never giving up” no matter what may come your way… choose to stay positive and get it done!</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-22 text-style\">Love Wins Every-time!!</h4>'),
