(1882, 35, 'feature_page', '<h4 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"##\">THE STORY BOOKS:</a></span> The Rainbow Race consists of 7 amusing books with captivating stories that can enlighten children, from the ages of 0 to 7 years old, on how to choose positive ways over negative ones. The stories encourage a child to choose the right way to handle a trying situation, when it comes up. These realistic stories actually happen to a lot of young children unbeknownst to parents at times. It is helpful to a child, at a young age, to know that most of them can choose their reactions to negative situations and that positive emotions can overcome negative ones. These stories can help parents and guardians to bring important awareness to their children in a fun, but constructive way.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"##\"> THE RAINBOW RACE (course)</a></span> is sold separate from the The Rainbow Race app. The course contains the 7 storybooks, their discussion pages, and its “Certificate of Completion” that is the reward for finishing the race. The Certificate of Completion will be available at the back of the 7th book. It is authentically signed by the author, Stella Gain and has a space for a child’s name and another adult’s signature, as a way to show a child that their accomplishment of finishing the 7 books (or the race) was important and is now official. This certificate also has words of affirmation on it, and can be a reminder to stay positive no matter what, which is its message. It is beneficial to a child to either frame this certificate or simply place it in a place where a child can be reminded to make positive choices. <span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"###\">Check out The Rainbow Race Store.</a></span></h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"##\">THE CERTIFICATE OF COMPLETION:</a></span> is a certificate given to a child at the end of the 7th book as a reward for finishing the race. At the end of each book there will be a code that an adult can input on the <a class=\"text-change\" href=\"###\">Record Your Child’s Progress</a> page (See the certificates at the bottom of this page) in order a keep a record of which level their child has reached. When all 7 codes have been recorded, an adult can download this certificate from the same page. The Certificate of Completion consists of affirmations such as: “I Choose to be a Winner!” “I Choose to be Happy!” or “I Choose Love! The adult can choose a certificate from these three affirmations; whichever certificate is appropriate for their child. The author, Stella Gain, has already signed it. It has a space for the child’s name and a space for a parent/guardian to also sign it as way to make it official for the child. This will make the child feel like they truly accomplished a beneficial goal. LWE Inc. recommends that a child display this certificate in their room in order to remind them to acknowledge or speak these words into their life on a regular basis, and even through troubling times. Words of affirmation have been proven to help a person stay positive and successful. <span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"###\">\"See Affirmations\"</a></span></h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"#\">THE DISCUSSION PAGES:</a></span> After reading each story, a discussion page is available for an adult and child to spend more quality time together. This page includes questions about the story and can help the child to further understand the message. There are also a few new words to learn. A valuable conversation can happen about the importance of these new words that appear in each story. A child can learn and understand important words in a fun way that will also help them to live a successful life.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"#\">THE RAINBOW RACE</a></span> (course) is sold separate from the app and contains the storybooks, their discussion pages, and its “Certificate of Completion” that is the reward for finishing the race. This certificate is authentically signed by the author, Stella Gain and has a space for a child’s name and another adult’s signature, as a way to show a child that their accomplishment of finishing the 7 books (or the race) was important and is now official. This certificate also has words of affirmation on it, and can be a reminder to stay positive no matter what, which is its message.</h4>\r\n<h5 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"#\">THE RAINBOW RACE GAMES:</a></span> At the end of each book, and once it is completed by a child, there is an entertaining game that a child can choose to play alone or with a friend. These games can be a bonus or an enjoyable way to help a child think and focus on a specific goal, helping them to strengthen their mental health from a young age. The games can help with utilizing their memory and brain muscles, which will help speed up the development of a young child’s mind, by keeping them occupied as they achieve. These constructive games encourage a child to keep going in order to finish the specific goals of the games.</h5>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4 padding\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"#\">THE RAINBOW RACE SONGS:</a></span> At the end of each book, and once it is completed there is a bonus song available that interprets the story in song form. A child can dance and sing along to the catchy choruses sung by children their own age, who are there to help them relate to the messages. Music and singing are proven tools to help a child’s brain develop at a rapid pace…these songs are bouncy and up-tempo for this very reason. These songs will help older children to memorize their words in order to perform the karaoke versions, if they wish.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"#\">KARAOKE:</a></span> After listening to the songs, older children may want to perform one of the songs themselves. These karaoke tracks are instrumentals and are available for a child to sing along to their favorite song, while boosting their confidence for the next stages of their life. These instrumental tracks have been slowed down in order for a child to keep up. Karaoke is a fun way to motivate a child to listen and remember in order to be focused and independent for future learning. A child can learn to read in a speedy fashion, helping them to be alert and full of energy. Karaoke can be a project for an adult and their child to play together. Get your singing skills ready! The instrumental tracks can also be an addition to a new baby’s healthy development. The karaoke tracks have beats and instruments that can stimulate a baby’s brain and development.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4\"><span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"#\">NAP TIME:</a></span> The author Stella Gain narrates each story in order for a child to listen to while they fall sleep. The stories repeat with Stella’s soothing voice helping a child to contentedly fall asleep. From a baby to a toddler these bedtime stories can help a child’s brain to develop proficiently, while they nap. Listening to readings and music are well known activities that help a baby/infant develop the muscles in their brain that they will need to use later to perfect the skills they choose. This feature can be reached any time and is not part of the actual Rainbow Race. We also recommend playing the karaoke tracks to babies and toddlers while they rest. The music on these empty tracks will stimulate their brains to be active and strong.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"text-h4\">A percentage of The Rainbow Race funds will go toward children’s charities, where every penny counts to help less fortunate children to survive.</h4>'),
