(2100, 39, 'wordofaffrimation', '<h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                              Words of affirmation are words that are either spoken or written in order to uplift, support and edify oneself or others. Some people believe that words of affirmation can bring success into people\'s lives when spoken regularly. Child experts confirm that teaching children to choose to be positive from a young age can bring them great success as adults. <i class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"###\">The Rainbow Race</a></i> can be a way for adults to guide their young children onto the road of healthy living. <span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"##\">See Endorsements</a></span>\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                              <span class=\"text-change\">Jennifer Lopez</span> has said that she spends 15 minutes every day dedicated to affirmations. She confirmed that affirmations have helped bring her success and have helped her to stay strong and positive.\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                              <span class=\"text-change\">Oprah Winfrey</span> went from poverty to becoming one of the world’s wealthiest and most successful women. She is one of the biggest believers and supporters of a positive mindset. She says that without affirmations, she would not have accomplished all that she has.\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h5 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                                 <span class=\"text-change\">Jim Carrey</span> in 1985, made a bold decision to write himself a $10-million check for “acting services rendered.” He dated it 10 years in the future and kept it in his wallet. He was rumored to regularly speak positive words over this check. It cannot be a coincidence that in 1995, Carrey found out he was cast in the movie “Dumb and Dumber.” And wonders never cease because ten years after writing the check, he was paid $10 million for this role!\r\n                            </h5>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                                 <span class=\"text-change\">Denzel Washington</span> stated that he is indebted to words of affirmation for his huge success. He also confirmed that he’s gotten over many personal problems by changing his ways and keeping a positive mindset.\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                                 <span class=\"text-change\">The Queen of England’s</span> long and successful life is an undeniable example of words of affirmation being put into practice and working. The UK’s national anthem begins with “God save our gracious Queen, Long live our noble Queen. God save the Queen.” Millions who love and respect the Queen have sung this anthem for decades, and it could be said that this is one of the reasons why the Queen has lived so long, and is still working hard in her mid-nineties with no signs of stopping. Could it be that these heartfelt words of her people, sung on a daily basis, have been a huge factor in her very long life? Are these words also rubbing off onto her husband, Prince Philip, who is 99 years old this year?! If so, speaking words into existence is indeed a powerful tool.\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                                 <span class=\"text-change\">Queen Elizabeth</span> is also known as “The Rainbow Queen” because of her legendary outfits, which are usually one color of the rainbow including the same color hat. She has been known to say that she purposefully does this for the many people who come to see her in order for her to easily stand out in the crowd. The Queen of England loves her people and encapsulates all aspects of affirmative thinking. She is one of the most successful, as well as one of the most respected people in the world.\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                                 <span class=\"text-change\">The Rainbow Race kids</span> have their own affirmation’s experience. The oldest Rainbow Race kid, Benjamin, who was 7 years old, when he took part in singing on the Rainbow Race songs went on to be an excellent basketball player. In fact, by the age of 11 years old, he was on a few US ranking lists and was actually number 1 in the nation on a couple of them. By his freshman year in high school, he was a top player in California and at the end of his freshman year he was #1 for his grade and position on several Maxpreps stat’s lists. Maxpreps.com is a site that records high school stats for all the sports in the America. He was actually #1 in the nation for double/doubles, field goals, free throws and others. Benjamin had a very bright future and kept exceling. Expert sport’s writers projected him to be in the Top 25 players of the class of 2020. However in his senior year, he suffered an ACL injury. It has been his positive attitude that has kept him going through this difficult injury. So far, he has kept his hope alive to keep on pursuing his goal. We are looking forward to his comeback. Follow his progress at @Benjamin.Todd”\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h5 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                                 After Benjamin became successful, we did not recognize a correlation with The Rainbow Race, but when the demo version of The Rainbow Race was first created, LWE uploaded Book 3 “If I Work Very Hard” onto Youtube.com in 2010. There were many views and comments, which can be seen at <span class=\"text-change\"><a href=\"book3.html\">Book 3 reviews</a></span> here at the site or this demo can also still be found at Youtube.com. We remembered that the chorus of the song says, “Someday you’ll be number 1!” The years after The Rainbow Race songs were produced in 2008, we observed Benjamin work very hard to reach his goals. He practiced almost daily just like the song advises in order to get to the top. He enjoyed this work because this was his dream career. He was rewarded for his hard work by the results of his game, and now he will not give up until he reaches his goal of going pro. This Rainbow Race kid has proven it can be done. No one can argue with this concept because it is a fact.\r\n                            </h5>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                               We do not need much more evidence that speaking affirmations work!\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <h4 class=\"text-h4\">\r\n                                We aim to help children learn about affirmations with our “Certificate of Completion.”\r\n                            </h4>'),
